This paper deals with the task of entity recognition in medical documents, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP). The proposed approach is based on neural networks and involves two subtasks: detecting overlapping spans and combining them into discontiguous entities. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, given the focus on NLP and neural networks, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
